Package fr.ybo.csvengine.annotation

This package contain all annotations used to map a class with a CSV File.

See:
          Description

Annotation Types Summary
CsvColumn Annotation used on attribute of class which is a column of CSV file

French : Annotation utilisée pour représenté une colonne csv.
CsvFile Annotation used to declare a class must mapped with a CSV File.
CsvParam Annotation used to contain a parameter for Adapter and Validator.
CsvValidation Annotation used to add a Validator on a CSV Column.
CsvValidations Annotation used to contain multiple CsvValidation.
 

Package fr.ybo.csvengine.annotation Description

This package contain all annotations used to map a class with a CSV File.
Declaration of a class :

 @CsvFile(separator = ";")
 public static class Exemple {
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_1", order = 0)
        private String attribut1;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_2", order = 1, adapter = AdapterBoolean.class)
        private Boolean attribut2;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_3", order = 2, adapter = AdapterDouble.class)
        private Double attribut3;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_4", order = 5, adapter = AdapterInteger.class)
        private Integer attribut4;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_5", order = 3, adapter = AdapterString.class)
        private String attribut5;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_6", order = 6, adapter = AdapterTime.class)
        private Integer attribut6;
 }
The Exemple class will correspond to the CSV File :
 att_1;att_2;att_3;att_4;att_5;att_6
 valeur1;0;0.25;3;valeur5;12:25


French : Ce package contient les annotations à utiliser pour mapper une classe avec un fichier CSV.
Déclaration d'une classe :
 @CsvFile(separator = ";")
 public static class Exemple {
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_1", order = 0)
        private String attribut1;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_2", order = 1, adapter = AdapterBoolean.class)
        private Boolean attribut2;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_3", order = 2, adapter = AdapterDouble.class)
        private Double attribut3;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_4", order = 5, adapter = AdapterInteger.class)
        private Integer attribut4;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_5", order = 3, adapter = AdapterString.class)
        private String attribut5;
        @CsvColumn(value = "att_6", order = 6, adapter = AdapterTime.class)
        private Integer attribut6;
 }
La classe Exemple correspondra au CSV suivant :
 att_1;att_2;att_3;att_4;att_5;att_6
 valeur1;0;0.25;3;valeur5;12:25
